                                                                                                               SPORT BRIEFS
                                        Bhambri advances   New Delhi: Wild card Yuki Bhambri eased into the pre-quarter finals of the ITF F3 Futures event here after a comfortable straight-set triumph over Israeli qualifier Saar Steele in the opening round of the $15,000 event Tuesday. Yuki sailed past Steele 6-2, 6-3 to set up a tough last-16 stage match against fourth-seed Hiroki Moriya of Japan.   Appeal filed  New Delhi: Tennis Australia Tuesday filed an appeal against the International Tennis Federation rsquo;s decision to approve Chennai as the venue for next month rsquo;s India-Australia Davis Cup tie. ITF will hear the appeal this week.  Prize hike  Wimbledon: Prize money is going up by 6.2 per cent at Wimbledon this year. Tournament organisers say the total prize fund will be pound;12.55 million for the June 22-July 5 tournament.   Heena silver  New Delhi: India rsquo;s Heena Sidhu Tuesday won the silver medal in the women rsquo;s air pistol event with an excellent score of 485.8 in the ISSF World Cup being staged at Beijing. The gold medal was won by Hu Jan of China while the bronze went to Maruskova Lenka of Czech Republic.   Drug testing  Turnberry (Scotland): Drug testing will be introduced at the British Open golf this year. Peter Dawson, chief executive of the Royal amp; Ancient organisers, said the players would be subject to the same anti-doping procedures that have been taking place for the past year on the main world tours.  
